snippet.textDisplay:
I just realized, I have never eaten normal Chili. Like, I can't eat high amounts of fat, so I'm replacing almost all my meat (that isn't chicken or fish) with soy stuff. I really love my chili sin carne, but now this feels weird. I need to eat a normal Chili con carne at least once in my life! (That being said, I also can't eat red beans, so I have to use white beans and I can't eat milk products, so no cheese for me. :(
But! I have to say an important thing:
Try making a pizza with this. Like, just put the chili mixture on a pizza and put cheese on top and put it in the oven. It tastes amazing! I did this once and it was worth the pain afterwards.
